== Singleton Design Pattern ==

Making the constructor privates ensures that you can never create a new object of that class.
Only one instance of that class would be created. This can be used for caches, thread pools, etc where
we need to have only one instance.

Multithreading is tricky when it comes to singleton classes.

Synchronized keyword makes sure that we don't encounter a race condition.

Undertaking the static initialization of the instance, which is guaranteed to be thread safe. 